					<div id="dsq-comment-body-227923" class="dsq-comment-body">
						<div id="dsq-comment-message-227923" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>I&#8217;d think the rule &#8220;find something that you enjoy doing&#8221; trumps all of those.</p>
<p>It took me a while to realize that, in spite of following most of your tips, in spite of seeing some results, regular weight lifting / cardio exercise in a gym IS boring, for me.</p>
<p>Now I cycle to work (found a nice route through a forest), do power yoga, and go to a climbing hall. Your mileage will vary.</p>
<p>I get much more exercise now than when I tried to get into a habit of going to the gym, and now I actually enjoy it! Makes it much easier to keep doing it regularly.</p>
